fr.n7.stl.tam.ast

Enum Library

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Library>
      • fr.n7.stl.tam.ast.Library
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TAMInstruction, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Library>

    public enum Library
extends java.lang.Enum<Library>
implements TAMInstruction
    Atomic operators provided by the TAM virtual machine for basic types : Boolean, Character, Integer, Memory and String.

      I2C
      Pops an Integer value from the stack, converts it to a Boolean (1 is true, 0 is false) and pushes that one on the stack.
      I2S
      Pops an Integer value from the stack, converts it to a String and pushes that one on the stack.
      IAdd
      Pops two Integer values from the stack, and pushes their sum on the stack.
      IDiv
      Pops two Integer values from the stack, and pushes their quotient (Euclidean division) on the stack.
      IEq
      Pops two Integer values from the stack, compares them and pushes the true Boolean value on the stack if they are equal and false if not.
      IGeq
      Pops two Integer values from the stack, compares them and pushes the true Boolean value on the stack if the first on is greater or equal than the second one and false if not.
      IGtr
      Pops two Integer values from the stack, compares them and pushes the true Boolean value on the stack if the first on is strictly greater than the second one and false if not.
      IIn
      Reads an Integer value from the console, and pushes it on the stack.
      ILeq
      Pops two Integer values from the stack, compares them and pushes the true Boolean value on the stack if the first on is lesser or equal than the second one and false if not.
      ILss
      Pops two Integer values from the stack, compares them and pushes the true Boolean value on the stack if the first on is strictly lesser than the second one and false if not.
      IMod
      Pops two Integer values from the stack, and pushes their rest (Euclidean division) on the stack.
      IMul
      Pops two Integer values from the stack, and pushes their product on the stack.
      INeg
      Pops an Integer value from the stack, and pushes its opposite on the stack.
      INeq
      Pops two Integer values from the stack, compares them and pushes the true Boolean value on the stack if they are different and false if not.
      IOut
      Pops an Integer value from the stack, and writes its value on the console.
      ISub
      Pops two Integer values from the stack, and pushes their subtraction on the stack.
      MAlloc
      Pops an Integer value from the stack, allocates a memory chunk of that value size in the heap, and pushes its address on the stack.
      MCompare
      Pops two Integer values from the stack that are addresses of memory chunks of the same size in the heap and one Integer value that is the size of these chunk, then it pushes on the stack a Boolean value that is the result of the comparison of both chunks.
      MCopy
      Pops two Integer values from the stack that are addresses of memory chunks of the same size in the heap and one Integer value that is the size of these chunk, then it copies the content of the first chunk in the second chunk.
      MFree
      Pops an Integer value from the stack that must be an address in the heap and free the associated memory chunk.
      MVoid
      Pushes the void address on the stack.
      S2B
      Pops an Integer value from the stack which is a String slot in the TAM virtual machine, converts the content of that String to a Boolean and pushes that one on the stack.
      S2C
      Pops an Integer value from the stack which is a String slot in the TAM virtual machine, converts the content of that String to a Character and pushes that one on the stack.
      S2I
      Pops an Integer value from the stack which is a String slot in the TAM virtual machine, converts the content of that String to an Integer and pushes that one on the stack.
      SAlloc
      Allocation a String slot in the TAM virtual machine and pushes the slot number on the stack.
      SConcat
      Pops two Integer values from the stack that are String slots in the TAM virtual machine, then it allocates a new String slot in the TAM virtual machine, copies the content of the two Strings in the new one and pushes the slot number of the new one on the stack.
      SCopy
      Pops two Integer values from the stack that are String slots of the same size in the TAM virtual machine then it copies the content of the first String in the second one.
      SIn
      Reads a String value from the console, and pushes it on the stack.
      SOut
      Pops a String value from the stack, and writes its value on the console.
